modules.description: Processes strings using a custom encoding by folding over each character and its position. Works with `string` values and an abstract encoding type. Useful for parsing or transforming encoded text where character positions are significant, such as in source code analysis or binary format decoding.

This module provides operations to validate, compare, and decode characters according to a specified encoding. It works with characters and Unicode values, supporting precise checks and transformations. Concrete use cases include validating character compatibility with encodings, comparing characters for equality or order, and decoding characters to their Unicode representation.

This module decodes text in various ISO 8859 encodings into Unicode, handling input from strings, channels, or manual sources. It provides precise control over decoding state and byte tracking, with support for malformed character detection. Use cases include parsing legacy encoded text files, converting character streams to Unicode, and analyzing byte-level input where encoding accuracy is critical.
